      "role": "user",
      "content": "it’s just hard to find the point sometimes. i was looking at some articles about the heat death of the universe and the scale of everything... it just makes everything i'm going through feel so incredibly stupid. like, why am i even trying to fix my life or deal with this pain when in a few billion years there won't even be a trace that any of this happened? it feels like i'm just performing this heavy, exhausting ritual of existing for no reason at all.",
